17:13.906 --> 17:15.366
Yes!
All right!

17:15.449 --> 17:16.951
Now that's
a winning combination.

17:19.118 --> 17:21.454
Here you go.
Front and center.

17:21.539 --> 17:23.082
I'm so proud of you, Homie.

17:23.165 --> 17:25.166
It's like you're Kid Rock...

17:25.251 --> 17:27.752
and I'm
Pamela Anderson Lee Rock.

17:27.836 --> 17:30.172
[Audience Cheering ]

17:30.256 --> 17:32.007
Oop. Gotta run. Enjoy the show.

17:34.176 --> 17:36.428
[Tuning UP]

17:36.512 --> 17:38.055
[ Rag Squeaking ]

17:38.138 --> 17:40.099
Okay. Let's see the eyes.

17:41.767 --> 17:43.936
Now the fire.

17:44.812 --> 17:46.313
[Sizzling]

17:47.231 --> 17:48.274
Thanks, mate.

17:48.357 --> 17:50.192
Couldn't you find
a more fuel-efficient Satan?

17:50.276 --> 17:51.986
Lenny, don't you have
a crotch to stuff?

17:53.070 --> 17:55.239
Evening, fellow rockers.
There you are.

17:55.322 --> 17:57.449
We thought we were going to
have to go on without you.

17:57.533 --> 17:59.201
I'm ready.
Just give me a guitar.

17:59.285 --> 18:00.995
How many solos
should I do? Four?

18:02.538 --> 18:04.123
<i>I'll do four.</i>

18:04.206 --> 18:07.793
Uh, Homer, you didn't think
you were gonna be <i>playing</i> with-

18:07.876 --> 18:11.338
[ Gasps ]
My official tour jacket! Lookit.

18:11.422 --> 18:12.923
Wait.

18:13.007 --> 18:14.967
You misspelled “guitar hero.”

18:15.050 --> 18:17.553
Look, sorry if there's been
a misunderstanding, Homer.

18:17.636 --> 18:22.099
We really just need you
to tap the mikes and say, “Test, test.”

18:22.182 --> 18:23.225
Can't you do it?

18:25.269 --> 18:27.688
Oh. Okay.

18:27.771 --> 18:29.315
<i>So I'll, uh-</i>

18:30.024 --> 18:31.400
Okay.

18:33.068 --> 18:35.696
[Audience Cheering ]

18:36.530 --> 18:37.990
Look, there's Dad!

18:38.073 --> 18:39.575
Whoo-hoo! Yay, Homer!

18:39.658 --> 18:41.702
I'm his groupie.
[Chuckles]

18:41.785 --> 18:43.370
Am I saying that right?
“Groupie”?

18:43.454 --> 18:44.788
[All]
Yeah!

18:44.872 --> 18:47.374
[Woman ]
Yeah, Homer!

18:47.458 --> 18:49.585
[ Carl ] You're the man, Homer!
You're the man!

18:49.668 --> 18:51.128
[Lenny] Rock the house!
Let's go, Homer!

18:51.211 --> 18:53.005
[ Moe ] It's go time.
It's go time.

18:53.088 --> 18:55.341
[ Microphone Feedback]
Test. Test.

18:55.424 --> 18:58.969
Why is he performing
the duties of a roadie?

18:59.053 --> 19:00.804
Am I saying that right? “Roadie”?

